I want to be able to take an entire repository and download all datasets (the vector datasets that I can currently support) and add them to the database. For example, pointing to https://egis-lacounty.hub.arcgis.com/search, should download all datasets there one-by-one. You should use the APIs available there [https://egis-lacounty.hub.arcgis.com/api/search/definition/]. When downloading a dataset, choose the most appropriate format available. GeoJSON seems to be a good format, if available, since it's flexible, but if there is an evidence that a specific format (that is currently supported) is the native or original one, we should use it.